Source: YCB Object and Model Set, Google scans (16k polygon variants).
Upstream: https://ycb-benchmarks.s3.amazonaws.com/data/google/<id>_google_16k.tgz
Project page: https://www.ycbbenchmarks.com/

The YCB Object and Model Set is made available under terms described at
https://www.ycbbenchmarks.com/ for research and educational use. The
nontextured STL geometry shipped here is derived from the Google-scanned
16k-polygon variants, re-centered (xy-centroid at origin, bottom at z=0),
exported as OBJ, and CoACD-decomposed into convex hulls for MuJoCo
contact simulation. Masses are sourced from the YCB project's
published object metadata.

If you are using RoboSandbox for commercial purposes or redistribution,
please consult the YCB project's terms directly.

Bundled objects (see each sub-directory's .robosandbox.yaml sidecar):
  003_cracker_box
  005_tomato_soup_can
  006_mustard_bottle
  011_banana
  013_apple
  024_bowl
  025_mug
  035_power_drill
  042_adjustable_wrench
  055_baseball

Reference:
  Calli, B., Singh, A., Walsman, A., Srinivasa, S., Abbeel, P., and
  Dollar, A. M. "The YCB Object and Model Set: Towards Common Benchmarks
  for Manipulation Research." International Conference on Advanced
  Robotics (ICAR), 2015.
